The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, March 12, 2004 				 Court slap
																								Calcutta, March 11: The high court today pulled up a government employee for not obeying a lower court order to pay Rs 1,800 every month to his separated wife and two minor children, who were virtually starving.																								Yudhistir Pramanik had challenged in high court the order that asked him to pay his ex-wife and children. Justice Arunabha Barua said: As a man, I am feeling ashamed. He asked the petitioner to pay Rs 37,800, the total amount due, immediately.
